In this chapter T. setteth downe the efficacie of true cō
                     linesse;





that it leadeth vnto the conuenience and preseruation of nature, beeing agreeable thereunto: And that following nature, we cannot erre; but wee shall both follow that which is acute & wittie, viz. prudence; and that which serueth for the increase of humane societie, to wit iustice; and likewise that which is truly valorous.

